    "created_at": "2014-11-30T10:26:38Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-11-30T10:26:38Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "after discussion with @tiagoantao: the issue is that the `max_colwidth` is not applied to the index, only to the columns (so it has nothing really to do with groupby, but because of the groupby, the columns became a multi-index).\n\n```\ndisplay.max_colwidth : int\n    The maximum width in characters of a column in the repr of\n    a pandas data structure. When the column overflows, a \"...\"\n    placeholder is embedded in the output.\n    [default: 50] [currently: 50]\n```\n\nSo literally, it is only applied to the columns, but I think it seems logical to also apply this maximum width to the index?\n"
  },
